posts.text:
전기차 News 2018년 새로운 전기차 라인업 공개 58분 전 URL 복사 본문 기타 기능 번역보기 http://blog.naver.com/evcar123/221134696262 전기 자동차의 성능 , 인프라가 빠르게 발전되고 있는 지금 , 차량 구매를 고민하신다면 내연기관이냐 전기 자동차냐의 갈림길에 서시는 분들이 많을 것 같습니다 . 하지만 1 회 충전 주행거리 400km 에 육박하는 전기 자동차들이 2018 년 출시를 앞두고 있다면 ? 조금은 더 후자 쪽에 무게를 싣고 지켜보실 분들이 많을 것 같습니다 . 올해보다 더욱 업그레이드되어 돌아오는 전기자동차들 ! 2018 년 출시 예정된 전기 자동차들을 소개 드립니다.
▶기아자동차 니로 EV
기아자동차에선 전기자동차 SUV 니로가 새롭게 출시될 예정입니다 . 아직까진 니로 전기 자동차의 구체적인 제원이나 특징은 밝혀지지 않아 정확한 정보를 드릴 순 없지만 , 기아 니로도 한번 충전으로 최대 380Km 이상 주행 가능할 것으로 소개되고 있습니다 .
현대 자동차 코나와 다른 성격을 띠는 점은 넓은 실내공간으로 가족 차량을 구매하고자 하는 분들에게 좋은 전기 자동차 선택지가 될 것 같습니다 . 기존 전기 자동차 대비 주행거리가 대폭 향상된 코나와 니로 외에도 도심 위주의 주행에 구매 목적이 맞춰져 있으시다면 주행거리 200km 대의 전기차도 구매 후보가 될 수 있습니다 .
▶ 현대자동차 코나 EV
현대자동차에서 출시 예정인 코나는 1 회 충전 시 서울에서 부산까지 거리인 약 390Km 를 주행할 수 있게 되었습니다 . 최신 기술의 적용으로 휠 디자인도 공기저항을 줄여 같은 힘으로 더 많은 거리를 주행할 수 있게 설계되었는데요 . 국내 출시 시점은 18 년도 4 월 예정이라고 합니다 .
▶르노삼성자동차 SM3 Z.E
르노삼성의 준중형 전기차 SM3 Z.E 가 업그레이드 되었습니다 .
2018 년 SM3 Z.E 는 1 회 충전 시 주행거리가 기존 135km 보다 213km 로 향상되었습니다. 배터리 용량을 무게 증가 없이 기존보다 63% 높은 35.9kWh 로 증량해 효율을 높였다고 하는데요 . 교통안전공단이 발표에 따르면 국내 승용차 1 일 평균 주행거리인 40Km 기준으로 1 회 충전으로 약 5 일간 주행할 수 있다고 합니다 .
▶한국 GM 쉐보레 볼트 EV
이미 GM 에서 출시한 볼트 EV 의 경우 한번 충전으로 최대 383Km 까지 주행 가능하여 가장 긴 공인 주행거리를 인정받았습니다 . 하루 40Km 주행 시 1 회 충전으로 1 주일을 주행할 수 있다고 하여 시판 2 시간 만에 2017 년 올해의 물량을 모두 소진하기도 했습니다 . 수요 예측의 실패로 올해는 많은 분들이 아쉬움만을 삼킬 수밖에 없었는데요 . 업계에 따르면 내년 판매 물량을 기존 수 백대에서 수 천대 수준으로 판매량이 확대될 예정이라고 합니다 . 그 외에 구체적인 판매 계획은 발표되지 않았습니다 .
▶BMW 자동차 BMWi3 94Ah
BMW 의 첫 전기차 i3 가 새롭게 업그레이드되어 올해 9 월 출시되었습니다 . 94Ah 용량의 리튬이온배터리를 탑재하여 완전 충전 시 , 기존 모델보다 약 50%가량 주행 가능 거리가 늘어났는데요 . 그 결과 향상된 배터리로 1 회 충전 시에 최대 208Km 까지 주행이 가능해졌습니다 .
이외에도 더 많은 주행거리를 달릴 수 있도록 발전된 기술로 찾아오는 쏘울 EV, 아이오닉 일렉트릭이 출시될 예정입니다 .
해가 다르게 발전하는 전기 자동차의 성능 소식에 더욱 많아질 도로 위의 전기 자동차와 파란 하늘을 상상하며 기분 좋은 기다림을 해봅니다 .

posts.title: POTENCIAL TURÍSTICO DA CIDADE
posts.text:
Leitores, dia quatro de novembro, o blog esteve conversando com o secretário de turismo, o Sr. Augusto Oliveira, que aproveitou o momento para falar de vários aspectos relacionados ao turismo local, incluindo a preparação para o carnaval e a resolução dos problemas dos barraqueiros de Morro Branco. Primeiramente, o blog fez uma pergunta sobre o projeto para o carnaval de 2018, ele afirmou que ainda está vendo com o senhor prefeito sobre essa possibilidade, na visão do edil Beberibe está passando por sérios momentos de dificuldades financeiras, neste sentido, não teria lógica o poder público gastar com carnaval, porém, a possibilidade não foi descartada. O blog também o questionou sobre a situação dos barraqueiros da comunidade de morro branco que vem passando por sérias dificuldades, e ele nos deu uma notícia muito importante, segundo ele o local onde vão ficar as novas barracas já teria sido resolvido, isso com certeza trarão muitas alegrias para a associação, para os barraqueiros e para as pessoas que precisam de emprego no comércio situado na orla marítima da cidade. O edil afirmou que no dia cinco de outubro, eles iriam se reunir na comunidade de Morro Branco com a presença de algumas autoridades da união, do estado e do município para discutir junto com os moradores a resolução dos problemas. A população espera que o poder público possa realmente ajudar essa pessoas, a comunidade de Morro Branco é conhecida mundialmente pela sua gastronomia, pelas areias coloridas, pelo passeio de bugue, artesanato e por tantas outras coisas que encantam os turistas. Аннотация 
Стандарты использования конусно-лучевой компьютерной томографии в различных разделах амбулаторной стоматологической практики, челюстно-лицевой хирургии и оториноларингологии. Практическое руководство-монография посвящено возможностям нового метода лучевой диагностики - конусно-лучевой компьютерной томографии (КЛ КТ, цифровой объемной томографии, трехмерной дентальной компьютерной томографии, 3Д КТ, дентальной объемной томографии), выполняемой с использованием различных видов дентальных компьютерных томографов. На материале обследования более 65 000 пациентов показаны диагностические возможности современнной конусно-лучевой компьютерной томографии в терапевтической, хирургической, ортопедической, детской стоматологии, имплантологии и ортодонтии, а также в челюстно-лицевой хирургии и оториноларингологии. Практическое руководство-монография может быть рекомендовано для врачей - лучевых диагностов, стоматологов, челюстно-лицевых хирургов, оториноларингологов, а также для подготовки специалистов в системе постдипломного профессионального образования. Стандарты применения конусно-лучевой компьютерной томографии в хирургической стоматологии, имплантологии и челюстно-лицевой хирургии; 4. Стандарты применения конусно-лучевой компьютерной томографии в детской стоматологии, ортодонтии, ортопедической стоматологии и гнатологии; 5. posts.title: Smoking, drinking associated with dental filling failure
posts.text:
/ Smoking, drinking associated with dental filling failure Smoking, drinking associated with dental filling failure It influences the chances of dental filling failure. Agencies   1:55 pm Tags: Dental filling No smoking Oral Health Quit smoking Smoking 
Smokers, drinkers, beware! As per a recent study, smoking and drinking influence the chance of dental filling failure. The research team also found that a genetic difference in some patients is associated with increased filling failure rates. The study also shows no major difference in filling failure rates between traditional amalgam and newer composite resin fillings. The results suggest that genetic analysis might help dentists to personalize treatments for their patients, which could lead to improved outcomes. Fillings can fail for a variety of reasons, including reemergence of the initial tooth decay or the filling becoming detached. Until now, the jury has been out on whether newer composite resin fillings are as durable as traditional amalgam fillings, which have been in use for more than 150 years but which contain mercury, a toxic metal. 
To investigate this, researchers from America and Brazil accessed a large repository of dental records from a dental school in Pittsburgh, which contained information on patient fillings and rates of failure up to five years after the filling procedure. The researchers found that overall, there were no major differences between patients receiving amalgam or composite fillings in terms of filling failure rates. This suggests that composite fillings are at least as durable as amalgam fillings, and offer a viable alternative with no toxic ingredients. The repository also contained information about patient lifestyles, including smoking and drinking habits, and a DNA sample from each patient — allowing the team to investigate whether patient lifestyle and genetic factors could affect the failure rate of composite fillings. Read here Dental fillings – what you need to know 
The team found that within two years of the procedure, fillings failed more often in patients who drank alcohol, and the overall filling failure rate was higher in men who smoked. Furthermore, a difference in the gene for matrix metalloproteinase (MMP2), an enzyme found in teeth, was linked to increased filling failure. The researchers hypothesize that MMP2 might be able to degrade the bond between the filling and the tooth surface, potentially leading to failure. While this link and preliminary hypothesis are intriguing, the researchers have not yet confirmed whether differences in the MMP2 gene are responsible for failed fillings, and will need to investigate this further. Read here can your teeth become sensitive after a cavity filling? 
However, the results suggest that personal factors for each patient appear to influence their chance of filling failure, rather than the filling material their dentist used. “A better understanding of individual susceptibility to dental disease and variation in treatment outcomes will allow the dental field to move forward,” says Alexandre Vieira, a researcher involved in the study. “In the future, genetic information may be used to personalize dental treatments and enhance treatment outcomes.” The findings have been published in journal Frontiers in Medicine .

코인 이니셜 목걸이는 사진에서 보이는 것과 같이
팬던트 위에 알파벳의 팬던트를 하나 더 착용해서 제작한답니다.
두개가 한번에 있으니 꼭 같은 사람이 시킨 주문같겠지만
전혀 다른 두분의 고객님께서 동일한 날에 주문해주신 제품들이랍니다.
거기다 두분다 팬던트만!
주문이 들어오고 제작을 시작할 때 너무너무 신기했답니다.
한 층 더 즐거워지는 기분이었달까요?
'B'가 달린 제품은 18K 제품이고, 'S'가 달린 제품은 14K 제품이랍니다.
사진으로 차이점이 느껴지실까요?!?!
솔직히.... 육안으로 보이는 제품에서는 별 차이 없답니다.
약간의 색상차이정도?
그러나! 금에서 가장 중요한 중량차이!!가 어마어마 하답니다.
'S'를 구매해주신 고객님께서는 앞면각인을 빼고 깔끔하게 알파벳으로 포인트를 강조해주셨어요.
'B'를 구매해주신 고개님께서는 아이의 이름을 각인하면서 좀 더 차이점을 두는 디자인으로
변경해주셨구요 :)
뒷면에는 두분 동일하게 아이의 이름과 보호자의 전화번호 2개!
이렇게 주문을 해주셨답니다.
넓은 코인 팬던트로 많은 내용의 각인이 들어가는 제품이라 저기저기 공간 남는거 보이나요?
이렇게 예쁘게 제작해서 고객님께 전달해 드렸는데
만족하셨을지 모르겠어요.
항상 두근두근한 마음이랍니다 :)
아이들과 함께 많은 추억을 쌓아갈 수 있었으면 좋겠어요♥
리뷰에 나온 제품문의는
블로그에 비밀댓글을 달아주시거나
페이지베베 사이트에 문의게시판에 남겨주시면
언제든 답변해 드립니다 :)

posts.title: Dos niños mueren al estrellarse un coche contra un colegio en Sídney
posts.text:
Black Friday Dos niños mueren al estrellarse un coche contra un colegio en Sídney El vehículo se metió en el aula de una escuela pública primaria en donde se encontraban 24 menores junto a su profesora EFE Sídney Martes, 7 noviembre 2017, 12:45 
Dos niños de ocho años murieron hoy después de que un coche se estrellara contra una clase en una escuela de primaria del suroeste de Sídney, en un incidente en que la Policía cree que no fue intencionado. 
Una mujer de 52 años estrelló su vehículo contra el aula de la escuela pública primaria Banksia Road, en donde se encontraban 24 niños junto a su profesora, según un comunicado de la Policía del estado de Nueva Gales del Sur. Los dos niños murieron tras ser trasladados al hospital infantil del oeste de Sídney a consecuencia de "múltiples traumas". 
Junto a estos dos menores también fueron internadas tres niñas, una en estado grave y las otras dos en condición estable, de acuerdo a las autoridades policiales. "Obviamente fue una escena de matanza (...) ha sido muy duro porque nosotros también somos padres", declaró a la cadena ABC Stephanie Radnidge, superintendente de las Ambulancias de Nueva Gales del Sur, que además atendieron en el lugar a 17 escolares y una profesora. 
La Policía informó de que la conductora salió ilesa y ha sido sometida a exámenes de sangre y orina para determinar las causas del accidente. "No creemos que haya sido un acto intencionado", comentó por su lado el comandante en funciones de la Policía de Nueva Gales del Sur, Stuart Smith, al explicar que se desconoce si la conductora tenía alguna relación con la escuela. ABD Başkanı Trump'tan Güney Kore'ye ziyaret ABD Başkanı Trump, Japonya'daki temaslarının ardından Asya turunun ikinci durağı Güney Kore'ye geçti. 07 Kasım 2017 Salı 09:33 
SEUL (AA) - ABD Başkanı Donald Trump , Japonya'daki temaslarının ardından Asya turunun ikinci durağı Güney Kore 'ye geçti. 
Trump'ı başkent Seul'ün 70 kilometre güneyindeki Osan Hava Üssü'nde Güney Kore Devlet Başkanı Moon Jae-in karşıladı. 
Güney Kore'nin Mavi Saray olarak da bilinen Devlet Başkanlığı Ofisi, Trump'ın ABD'nin bölgedeki askeri üssü Camp Humphreys'i ziyaret edeceğini açıkladı. Burada düzenlenecek öğlen yemeğinin ardından iki ülke askeri yetkilileri, ABD Başkanı Trump'a brifing verecek. 
Daha sonra başkent Seul'e geçecek Trump için Mavi Saray'da karşılama töreni düzenlenecek. Törenin ardından ABD ve Güney Kore liderleri görüşecek. 
Mayıs ayında göreve gelen Moon, ilk kez ülkesine resmi ziyarette bulunan bir devlet başkanını Mavi Saray' dışında karşıladı. 
Bu arada Trump'ın ziyareti, Kuzey Kore'nin 3 Eylül'deki altıncı nükleer denemesi sonrası bölgede oluşan gergin atmosfere rastladı. 
Eski ABD Başkanı George H. W. Bush'un 1992'deki turundan sonra en uzun Asya turuna çıkan Trump, pazartesi günü Japonya ile başladığı 13 günlük turunun ikinci durağı olan Güney Kore'de iki gün kalacak. 
Seul'ün ardından 8-9 Kasım'da Çin'de temaslarda bulunacak Trump, 10-12 Kasım'da Vietnam'ı ve 12-13 Kasım'da Filipinler'i ziyaret edecek.

posts.title: Louvre Abu Dhabi prepares to unveil itself to the world - FederalNewsRadio.com
posts.text:
November 7, 2017 2:26 am 5 min read Share 
ABU DHABI, United Arab Emirates (AP) — Stepping into the Louvre Abu Dhabi, one of the first artworks a visitor sees is a two-headed Neolithic statue from Jordan, one of the oldest known in human history. 
That duality — looking back and toward the future, encompassing both East and West — is a theme that extends throughout the new museum, which is opening to the public on Saturday after a decade of delays and questions over laborers’ rights. 
The conservative mores of Abu Dhabi, the capital of the United Arab Emirates that’s more buttoned-up than freewheeling Dubai, can be seen in the relative absence of pieces depicting nudity. Still, artwork at the new Louvre offers a brief history of the world and its major religions, not shying away from Judaism in a country that officially does not recognize Israel. 
“Here at the Louvre Abu Dhabi, we’ve accomplished history,” Mohamed Khalifa al-Mubarak, the chairman of Abu Dhabi Tourism and Culture Authority, said at a ceremony for journalists on Monday. “This museum is a lot more than just a museum.” 
Federal Insights: Learn how agency and industry experts are implementing federal data strategies. Advertisement 
The modernist museum, designed by French architect Jean Nouvel, sits under a honeycombed dome of eight layers of Arab-style geometric shapes. 
It draws the lapping waters of the Persian Gulf into its outer corridors, allowing individual beams of light that pass through the roof to strike the surface and cast dancing reflections across the white walls. At night, light inside pours out like tiny little stars from a salt shaker against the city’s skyline. 
“I imagine this metaphor of the sky, cosmic, cosmographic, with a random system like the stars itself,” Nouvel told The Associated Press. “I imagine that with not a lot of lighting, just a little bit to create a kind of rain of light.” 
That rain has been a long time coming in this desert country, a federation of seven sheikhdoms on the Arabian Peninsula. Authorities first announced the Louvre Abu Dhabi project in 2007 as Dubai feverishly built the world tallest building and other wonders. 
Today, much of Saadiyat Island, envisioned as a cultural district anchored by the museum, is still empty. A planned Middle East outpost of the Guggenheim remains unbuilt , with just a poured foundation on the salt flood plain. 
Part of the reason is the drop in global energy prices from over $100 a barrel in 2014 to around $30 in early 2016. Officials in Abu Dhabi have not disclosed how much it cost to build the museum. 
What is known is that Abu Dhabi agreed to pay France $525 million for the use of the “Louvre” name for the next 30 years and six months, plus another $750 million to hire French managers to oversee the 300 loaned works of art. A center at Paris’ Louvre now bears the name of the late UAE President Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan, which was also part of the deal. 
During construction, the project faced intense criticism over conditions faced by laborers, who faced low pay, long hours and hot conditions. A worker was killed in an accident in 2015 while another died of “natural causes” in 2016, according to Abu Dhabi authorities. 
Hundreds working on projects on the island, including the Louvre, also were deported or lost their work visas for launching strikes over their conditions, according to according to a 2015 Human Rights Watch report . Labor strikes are illegal in the UAE. 
Jean-Luc Martinez, the president-director of the Louvre in Paris, contends the museum spoke “very frankly” about laborer conditions. He described the museum as a bridge between Asia, Africa and Europe. 
“We are not a European museum,” he told the AP. “It’s a place to see the world from Abu Dhabi.” 
That begins in the first gallery, where the floor bears an outline of the UAE with the names of different world cities in Arabic, China, English and Hindi. Different cultures face each other in exhibits: for example, a French suit of armor is positioned to look directly across from a Japanese warrior’s outfit. 
The museum also makes a point to put the world’s religions side by side. 
In one exhibit, a Jewish funerary stele from France in 1250 sits next to a Tunisian Muslim’s funerary steel and a Christian archbishop’s stone epitaph from Tyre, Lebanon. A painted French stone statue of Virgin and Child stands by a section of a Syrian Quran dating to around 1250, open to a page recounting the night during the holy month of Ramadan when Muslims believe the holy book was revealed to the Prophet Muhammad. 
In a darkened room, a page from the Blue Quran, one of the oldest ever found, sits near a Gothic Bible, Buddhist sutras and a Torah from Yemen dating to 1498. 
In a Middle East still torn by religious and sectarian conflict, whether between Sunni and Shiite or Israelis and the Palestinians, simply putting them side by side is a major statement. 
“By addressing their message to all humanity without distinction, Buddhism, Christianity and Islam transcended local cultural characteristics and deeply transformed ancient societies,” one placard reads. “These religions shared with Judaism the concept of monotheism but diverged on the subjects such as the representation of the divine.” 
Nudity, however, is only lightly represented, either in bare breasts on an Italian dish or nude bronze ballerina statuettes by Edgar Degas, seemingly dancing in the line of sight of James McNeill Whistler’s famed painting of his mother. Whistler’s painting joins a woman’s portrait on wood by Leonardo da Vinci, two works by Pablo Picasso and a hot-pink Andy Warhol image of an electric chair. 
For now at least, the museum’s exhibit ends with an installation by Chinese artist Ai Weiwei called “A Foundation of Light,” an illuminated work of steel and glass that recalls the museum’s gleam at night.

Our ladies did the country proud by clinching the Asia Cup hockey tournament on November 5. 
A cash reward of Rs 1 lakh was awarded to each player and there is no doubt they deserved it. But is it enough? 
AFP 
Let's be honest, the amount is way below par. Let's look at two recent accomplishments by women in Indian sports. 
The Indian cricket team led by Mithali Raj reached the World Cup, mind it they did not win, but ended as finalists. Guess how much they got? A whopping Rs 50 lakh per person! 
AFP 
PV Sindhu finished with a silver medal at the Rio Olympics last year. She got a total cash reward worth Rs 13 crore! 
Well that speaks for itself. Not enough for our hockey girls, that's for sure. Why? Surely by now we should wake up and recognise achievements for what they are.

posts.text:
凤凰网汽车讯 日前，领克汽车正式宣布旗下的首款车型——领克01将在11月17日开幕的广州车展上开启预售。据悉，新车先期上市的均为搭载2.0T涡轮增压发动机的车型，并提供两驱和四驱版本供消费者选择。据此前的消息，2.0T车型的预售价区间为17-24万元。同时，新车还将于11月底（或为11月28日）在国内正式上市销售此外。此次，领克官方还透露了关于该车的部分配置信息。
外观方面，车头厚重感很强，大灯隐藏在贯穿式前进气格栅中，配合发动机盖两侧的“北极之光”LED行车灯，整体造型视觉冲击感很强。车身整体增添了众多个性化装饰，包括黑色车顶、银色行李架、倒置的鲨鱼鳍天线、双色轮毂等，让新车看上去更显年轻时尚。车身尺寸方面，新车长宽高尺寸为4512×1857×1673毫米（含行李架），轴距为2734毫米。
内饰方面，领克01采用略向驾驶者倾斜的设计，配备一体式的运动座椅。大量的撞色以及双缝线设计体现极强的档次感，而细节设计以及工艺确实与沃尔沃现有的车型不相上下。
领克01充满科技感的驾驶舱内，拥有同级别最大尺寸的10.2英寸中央触控屏和10.25英寸全液晶智能仪表盘。这两个屏幕可与手机形成三屏互动，在WiFi热点、终身免费4G数据流量、语音控制系统（带语音唤醒功能）以及20G车载硬盘等软硬件的支持下，消费者可通过Carplay和Carlife，以及近10个智能互联App（包括大众点评、新浪新闻等）实现与车辆的实时互联，还可对车辆进行远程控制。
配置方面，领克 01将配备电子换挡杆、EPB电子驻车、AutoHold自动驻车、Start & Stop智能启停系统、后泊车雷达、前排预警限力式安全带、车辆被盗提醒和追踪、被盗车辆启动限制等诸多安全配置，带行人识别功能的AEB主动式刹车系统时刻将行车危险化解于萌芽状态，带排队功能的ACC自适应巡航系统将驾驶者从繁琐的驾驶疲劳感中解放出来，使日常驾车如同置身于安全、自由的空间。
新车基于由沃尔沃汽车主导，吉利汽车与沃尔沃汽车联合开发的CMA中级车基础模块架构打造，与沃尔沃未来的XC40共享CMA平台。动力方面，领克01将率先搭载源自Drive-E系列的VEP4 2.0T涡轮增压发动机，该发动机的最大功率为140千瓦，峰值扭矩为300牛米，并包含两驱及四驱版本可选。此外，未来该车还将推出1.5T三缸发动机。传动方面，新车将提供6速手动、6速自动和7速双离合三种变速器。

FINANCIAL MARKETS 
Asian stocks rise after Wall Street gains, oil surges 
BEIJING (AP) — Asian stocks surged today after Wall Street posted modest gains on deal reports and turmoil in Saudi Arabia sent crude prices soaring. 
Chipmakers surged after Broadcom offered to buy competitor Qualcomm for $103 billion, which if completed would be the largest tech acquisition ever. Reports that Sprint’s owner, Japanese conglomerate SoftBank, might buy cable company Charter hammered shares of telecom giants AT&T and Verizon, which might face tougher competition. Sellers of household goods slumped on weak quarterly results from CVS Health and food distributor Sysco. The Standard & Poor’s 500 index rose 0.1 percent to 2,591.13. The Dow Jones industrial average added less than 0.1 percent to 23,548.42. The Nasdaq composite gained 0.3 percent to 6,786.44.

A wave of arrests of princes and other officials in what the Saudi leadership says is an anti-corruption crackdown sent shockwaves through global oil markets, pushing prices to two-year highs. Benchmark U.S. crude then slipped slightly but remained above $57 per barrel. 
The dollar gained against the yen and the euro. 
ASIA-TRUMP-WARY BUSINESS 
Businesses brace for the unexpected on Trump’s Asia tour 
HONG KONG (AP) — Some businesses in Asia are bracing for the unexpected as President Donald Trump traverses the region and meets with the leaders of major U.S. trading partners. Exporters are apprehensive, given Trump’s penchant for unpredictability, his vehement dislike for swollen U.S. trade deficits, and his threats to rip up trade deals. 
Trump began his tour in Japan, where he vowed to reshape the trading relationship, saying it’s “not fair and it’s not open.” He arrived in South Korea on Tuesday and will next travel to China, Vietnam and the Philippines, including stops at three regional summits. That allows him plenty of chances to showcase his assertive style and make off-the-cuff remarks that could leave his hosts and adversaries scrambling to react. 
INDONESIA-WHATSAPP 
Indonesia threatens to block WhatsApp over sexual content 
JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) — Indonesian authorities say they will block access to the popular WhatsApp instant messaging app if it doesn’t remove sexually explicit content. 
The Ministry of Communications and Information Technology said Tuesday on its website that it has already asked internet companies to block domain names used by Tenor, which provides animated image files known as GIFs through WhatsApp. 
The government has sent three notices to WhatsApp, which is owned by Facebook and widely used in Indonesia, asking it to remove pornographic content and will block the app if there’s no response by Wednesday. 
Indonesia blocked web versions of the messaging app Telegram in July because it included chat groups for Islamic State group supporters. It lifted the partial ban after Telegram co-founder Pavel Durov visited Indonesia in August and agreed on efforts to remove radical content. 
Facebook’s Asia spokeswoman Charlene Chian said that WhatsApp can’t monitor their content because communications on the app are encrypted. 
Indonesia, the world’s most populous Muslim nation, has strict anti-pornography laws. 
THE DAY AHEAD 
Job opening survey to be released 
WASHINGTON (AP) — The Labor Department today will release a report on job openings and labor turnover, while the Federal Reserve will issue a report on consumer credit data for September. 
National unemployment has reached a 17-year low of 4.1 percent. The October jobs report, released last Friday, showed that pay gains remain sluggish, and the explanations include weak worker productivity and a still-low proportion of adults with jobs. Bu employers did add a solid 261,000 jobs. This happened, at least in part, because many businesses in Texas and Florida re-opened after having been forced to shut down in September when Hurricanes Harvey and Irma struck. 
CONGRESS-TAXES 
House tax panel adopts GOP changes after day of bickering 
WASHINGTON (AP) — A key House panel working on an overhaul of the tax code has restored the exemption from taxes for employees receiving child care benefits from their companies. But the Ways and Means also put new requirements on a tax credit used by working people of modest means. 
The committee voted 24-16 along party lines to adopt the amendment from its chairman, Rep. Kevin Brady, a Texas Republican. The changes were made to the complex GOP tax legislation put forward last Thursday. 
The vote on the amendment capped a marathon session in which Republicans and Democrats argued heatedly over the nearly $6 trillion tax bill. Democrats repeatedly lodged objections to the bill, especially to its limits on prized deductions for homeowners and its repeal of the child adoption credit and the deduction for medical expenses. 
FEDERAL RESERVE-DUDLEY 
Dudley retirement reflects broad turnover of Fed leadership 
WASHINGTON (AP) — A revamping of the Federal Reserve’s leadership is widening with the announcement that William Dudley, president of the New York Fed and the No. 2 official on the Fed’s key interest rate panel, will retire next year. 
Just last week, President Donald Trump chose Fed board member Jerome Powell to replace Janet Yellen as Fed chair in February. The post of Fed vice chair remains vacant. So do two additional seats on the Fed’s seven-member board. And a fourth seat may open as well next year. 
The unusual pace of the turnover has given Trump the rare opportunity for a president to put his personal stamp on the makeup of the Fed, which operates as an independent agency. Investors are awaiting signals of how Trump’s upcoming selections might alter the Fed’s approach to interest rates and regulations. 
APPLE-TAX HAVEN 
Report: Apple revamped overseas ops to find new tax havens 
UNDATED (AP) — Apple revamped its overseas subsidiaries to take advantage of tax loopholes on the European island of Jersey after a crackdown on Ireland’s loose rules began in 2013. That’s according to reports in The New York Times and the International Consortium of Investigative Journalists. 
The news outlet and the nonprofit investigative organization cited confidential records that were obtained by the German newspaper Suddeutsche Zeitung (“ZOOT-doi-cheh DZEYE-tung”) and shared. The cache of 13 million secret documents came from Appleby, a Bermuda-based law firm that helps businesses and wealthy individuals find tax shelters. 
The moves came after a U.S. Senate subcommittee found in 2013 that Apple had avoided tens of billions of dollars in taxes by using overseas havens. The paper said Apple has $128 billion in offshore profits not taxed by the U.S. 
AMERICAN AIRLINES-DISABILITY SETTLEMENT 
American Airlines settles disabilities case for $9.8 million 
FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) — American Airlines and a subsidiary will pay $9.8 million in stock to settle claims that they failed to help disabled employees return to work. 
Federal officials say American and Envoy Air fired or put some workers on unpaid leave instead of making reasonable efforts to reassign them. 
The workers’ disabilities ranged from cancer to back and knee injuries. 
A lawsuit and consent agreement were filed Friday in federal district court in Phoenix by the U.S. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission for 12 named former workers and others in similar circumstances. The agency says violations of the 1990 Americans with Disabilities Act occurred from 2009 until August 2015. 
HASLAMS INVESTIGATION 
Prosecutors: ‘Infection of fraud’ at Haslam truck stop chain 
CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) — Federal prosecutors have outlined their case against former Pilot Flying J executives and sales representatives. They said the prosecution was the result of an “infection of fraud” at the truck stop chain controlled by the family of Cleveland Browns owner Jimmy Haslam and Tennessee Gov. Bill Haslam. 
Assistant U.S. Attorney David Lewen told jurors in his opening statement Monday that the four defendants participated in a widespread scheme to undercut competitors, boost company profits and reap the rewards in terms of personal compensation. 
Lewen said the case will show that the sales team set out to target unsophisticated trucking customers they deemed unlikely to recognize they weren’t receiving their negotiated rebates, and to furnish them with manipulated invoices if they started asking questions. 
ANTHEM-CEO 
Anthem picks former UnitedHealth executive to become CEO 
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) — Blue Cross-Blue Shield insurer Anthem has picked a former top executive from its biggest competitor to replace Joseph Swedish as its next CEO. 
Anthem said Monday that Gail K. Boudreaux will start Nov. 20. Swedish will serve as executive chairman until May and then as senior adviser for a couple more years. 
A statement Monday from Indianapolis-based Anthem Inc. gave no reason for the departure of Swedish. But a company spokeswoman said the change has been part of succession planning by the company’s board of directors for more than a year. 
Company shares jumped Monday after Anthem laid out that plan. 
TARGET-HOLIDAY HOURS 
Target to offer shoppers a breather after Thanksgiving 
NEW YORK (AP) — Target is offering shoppers a breather after holiday shopping on Thanksgiving. 
The Minneapolis-based discounter says it will open at 6 p.m. on Thanksgiving and then close at midnight local time. Its stores will then reopen at 6 a.m. local time on Friday until 10 p.m., 11 p.m. or midnight local time. 
That’s different from last year, when it kept stores open through the night. 
Target again will offer Black Friday deals at Target.com on the morning of Thanksgiving. In a lead-up to the holiday, it will dangle select deals starting Monday, as it has for the past four years. 
SINCLAIR BROADCAST-TRIBUNE MEDIA 
Maryland AG: Sinclair, Tribune TV merger is a ‘bad deal’ 
ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) — Maryland’s attorney general opposes the proposed merger between Sinclair Broadcasting Group and rival TV station operator Tribune Media. 
Attorney General Brian E. Frosh filed comments Friday with the Federal Communications Commission, arguing that the merger would lead to fewer options for consumers and higher prices. 
Frosh also asked the FCC to delay its decision on the merger until a court decides how to calculate national audience reach. 
Hunt Valley, Maryland-based Sinclair is already the nation’s largest local TV station operator with 173 stations. The Tribune deal, plus other pending acquisitions, would give it a total of 233 stations. 
Sinclair says the merger would make it more efficient and would help the survival of free, over-the-air TV. 
BROADCOM-QUALCOMM 
Broadcom offers $103 billion for Qualcomm in chip megadeal 
NEW YORK (AP) — Broadcom made an unsolicited, $103 billion offer for rival chipmaker Qualcomm, the tech industry’s largest attempted takeover that is destined to come under intense regulatory scrutiny. 
The company said Monday that it would not have pushed forward with the proposed buyout if it was not confident that its global customers “would embrace” the deal. 
It was not clear who Broadcom was referring to, but Apple is Qualcomm’s biggest customer. Qualcomm and Apple have been locked in a long running legal battle, with Apple refusing to pay any royalties owed to Qualcomm for some of the features in the iPhone. 
Industry analysts believe that if Apple does not challenge the deal, it’s one hurdle that Broadcom will have cleared. Related Topics

KTM, Indian Motorcycles, Harley-Davidson and lot more manufacturers are going to reveal new and exciting motorcycles. The EICMA 2017 show is about to begin shortly. posts.text:
파이코일바이오텍코리아㈜(대표 임창순)는 지난 3~5일 삼성동에서 열린 ‘코엑스 베이비페어’에 참가했다고 밝혔다.
이 회사는 미세조류를 인공 배양해 오메가3 DHA를 생산하고 있는 업체다. 오메가3는 혈관관리에 좋다고 알려져 심혈관계 질환, 눈 건강, 혈중 중성지질 및 혈행 개선, 기억력 개선에 도움을 받고 싶은 중년층에서 노년층까지 특히 선호하는 건강보조식품이지만 제품 선택 시 몇가지 고려해야 할 게 있다. 우선 불포화지방산이다 보니 온도 및 공기 노출에 따른 산패에 취약하다. 따라서 제조업체와 소비자가 가까우면 가까울수록 좋다. 아울러 생산추출방법도 반드시 확인해야 한다. ‘저온고압추출’이나 ‘저온초임계추출’ 방식으로 생산된 제품을 선택하는 것이 좋다.
오메가3 DHA를 선보인 파이코일바이오텍코리아/사진=김수종 에디터 이와 관련해 파이코일바이오텍코리아는 미세조류를 배양해 DHA를 생산하는 업체로 국제특허기술로 국내에서 오메가3를 생산하고 있다.
‘파이코어 DHA플러스900’은 불포화지방산의 특성을 고려해 국내 생산으로 신선함에서 차별성을 띠며, 식물성 미세조류를 배양해서 추출하기 때문에 오염물질의 위험에서 비교적 안전하다고 회사 측은 밝혔다.
